column1: NB: Up until Day 133 2016 the midnight summary was at 2400, end of day.
Program changed and no Day 133 summary. Day 135 to Day 138 became a summary at 0 at beginning of day, so both daily max and min need to be backdated
Day 138 to Day 146 2016 back to 2400 summary. From Day 147 onwards data is from NIWA server and a 0 hour summary so data needs to be backdated

column10: Summary becomes 0, so essentially it is the 2400 summary for the previous day, needs to be backdated
NIWA didn't load battery volts into summary
